definition.value: A branched glucosamine oligosaccharide comprising three beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-[beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl-(1->6)]-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine tetrasaccharide units connected via (1->3) head-to-tail linkages.
A trisaccharide composed of an alpha-L-rhamnosyl residue linked (1->2) to a beta-D-galactosyl residue which is in turn linked (1->4) to beta-L-rhamnose.
A branched tetrasaccharide derivative consisting of beta-L-rhamnose having a 3-O-phosphono-beta-D-glucosyl-(1->4)-[alpha-L-rhamnosyl-(1->2)]-beta-D-galactosyl moiety attached at the 4-position.
An N(6)-acyl-L-lysine derivative in which the acyl group is L-homocysteinyl.
Any fatty aldehyde with one double or triple bond located at any position in the aliphatic chain.
A dipeptide formed from L-lysyl and L-alanyl residues.
A 2-demethylmenaquinol whose structure comprises a benzohydroquinone nucleus and a side chain of eight isoprenoid units.
A tripeptide formed between L-Hcy, L-Lys and L-Ala in a linear sequence, with the peptide bond between Hcy and Lys being from the carboxy group of the Hcy to the epsilon-nitrogen of the lysine.
A dipeptide in which the carboxy group of L-homocysteine forms an amide bond with the epsilon-nitrogen of N(alpha)-acetylated L-lysine
A dipeptide in which the carboxy group of L-homocysteine forms an amide bond with the alpha-nitrogen of N(epsilon)-acetylated L-lysine.
A tripeptide formed between L-Hcy, L-Lys and L-Leu in a linear sequence, with the peptide linkage between Hcy and Lys being from the carboxy group of the Hcy to the epsilon-nitrogen of the lysine.
Any cyclic ketone that is derived from acridone.
A branched tripeptide in which L-homocysteine and L-valine are linked via peptide bonds to the epsilon- and alpha-nitrogens respectively of L-lysine.
Any compound derived from a benzopyridoquinolizidine.
A pentapeptide in which L-homocysteine is connected to tetralysine via a peptide bond to the epsilon-nitrogen of the N-terminal lysine residue.
Zwitterionic form of N-methyl-L-phenylalanine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
An alpha-amino-acid residue formed from N-methyl-L-phenylalanine
Zwitterionic form of N-methyl-L-methionine arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
An alpha-amino-acid residue formed from N-methyl-L-methionine.
An N-acylglycinate arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group of N-acetylglycine; major species at pH 7.3.
An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from  N-acetylglycine.
An N-acyl-L-alpha-amino acid anion arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group of N(alpha)-acetyl-L-arginine; major species at pH 7.3.
An alpha-aminoacyl group formed by loss of OH from the carboxy group of N(alpha)-acetyl-L-arginine.
An alpha-amino-acid residue formed from N(5)-methyl-L-glutamine.
A tetracarboxylic acid anion that results from the removal of a proton from all four carboxylic acid groups of dipyrrolylmethanemethyl-L-cysteine residue. Major species at pH 7.3.
The L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion that results from the transfer of a proton from the carboxylic acid group to the alpha-amino group of L-6'-bromotryptophan. The major species at pH 7.3.
Any ester of L-cysteine.
A dolichyl diphosphooligosaccharide in which the oligosaccharide moiety is the Man1GlcNAc2 linear trisaccharide beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc.
An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from N(omega),N(omega)-dimethyl-L-arginine.
An alpha-amino-acid residue cation resulting from the protonation of the imine nitrogen of N(omega),N(omega)-dimethyl-L-arginine residue.
A dolichyl diphosphooligosaccharide in which the oligosaccharide moiety is the Man2GlcNAc2 linear tetrasaccharide alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc.
An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from L-6'-bromotryptophan.

A dolichyl diphosphooligosaccharide in which the oligosaccharide moiety is the Man3GlcNAc2 branched pentasaccharide alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc.

A dolichyl diphosphooligosaccharide in which the oligosaccharide moiety is the Man5GlcNAc2 branched heptasaccharide alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc.
A fatty-acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of any hydroxy fatty acid.
A fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of any oxo-fatty acid.
The alkanesulfonate that is the anion formed from isethionic acid by loss of a proton from the sulfo group; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of any short-chain fatty acid.

A dolichyl diphosphooligosaccharide in which the oligosaccharide moiety is the Man6GlcNAc2 branched octasaccharide alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc.
A fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of any medium-chain fatty acid.

An EC 1.14.13.* (oxidoreductase acting on paired donors, incorporating 1 atom of oxygen, with NADH or NADPH as one donor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of nitric oxide synthase (EC 1.14.13.39).
An alkanesulfonate in which the alkyl group directly linked to the sulfonate functionality is ethyl.
A fatty acyl-CoA in which the fatty acyl group has a chain length greater than C22.
An alkanesulfonate in which the alkyl group directly linked to the sulfonate functionality is butyl.
A fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of any branched-chain fatty acid.
An amino acid zwitterion obtained from N(omega),N'(omega)-dimethyl-L-arginine by transfer of a proton from the carboxylic acid group to the alpha-amino group.

A dolichyl diphosphooligosaccharide in which the oligosaccharide moiety is the Man7GlcNAc2 branched nonasaccharide alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc.
An alpha-amino-acid residue derived from N(omega),N'(omega)-dimethyl-L-arginine.
A 2-(2,6-dioxopiperidin-3-yl)-1H-isoindole-1,3(2H)-dione that has R-configuration at the chiral centre.
A 2-(2,6-dioxopiperidin-3-yl)-1H-isoindole-1,3(2H)-dione that has S-configuration at the chiral centre.
